<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Acting Secretary of State to
                        the Ambassador in Ecuador</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v11</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d718</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">718</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-04-02T15:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-04-02T15:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-02T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-02T15:00:00-05:00" n="718" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d718">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24522/4–246: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Ambassador</gloss> in Ecuador</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-02T15:00:00-05:00">April 2, 1946—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>127. Galo Plaza yesterday presented Dept with note formally requesting withdrawal
                    from Galápagos at earliest possible moment.</p>
                <p>Dept asking War and Navy to set date. You will be kept advised of
                        developments.<note n="38" xml:id="d718fn38">The Department advised the
                        Ambassador in telegram 135, April 4, 1946, 7 p.m., that July 1, 1946, was
                        the date set for complete withdrawal (811.24522/4–446).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
